The paper deals with programming a robot to manipulate objects, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves generating a diverse repertoire of behaviors through simulation, which involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The approach also involves updating the existing solution repertoire with tests done on a real robot, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
